{
  "text": "Zebrafish (Danio rerio) were maintained and bred under standard conditions as previously described [CITATION_1] . Stages of embryonic development were determined according to their morphology [CITATION_2] . Embryos were treated with 0.003% 1-phenyl-2-thiourea (PTU) in egg water to prevent the production of pigment. The transgenic line Tg(HuC:GFP) was used in this study, in which the zebrafish brain is labeled with green fluorescent protein (GFP) [CITATION_3] . All animal experiments were approved by the Institutional Animal Care and Use Committee, Fudan University.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "82916201",
    "[CITATION_2]": "82916201",
    "[CITATION_3]": "38601026"
